# Code of Conduct

## Introduction

Our goal is to provide a welcoming and respectful environment for all contributors, regardless of their experience, gender, sexual orientation, physical appearance, race, or religion. This Code of Conduct applies to all spaces of the project and interactions among community members.

## Acceptable Behavior

- Treat everyone with respect and consideration.
- Use inclusive language and avoid derogatory comments.
- Collaborate and offer constructive criticism.
- Respect others' opinions and experiences.

## Unacceptable Behavior

- Use of sexualized language or any form of harassment.
- Derogatory comments or personal attacks.
- Constant interruptions in conversations.
- Intimidation or harassment in any form.

## Consequences

Behaviors that violate this Code of Conduct may result in disciplinary actions, which can include:

- Verbal or written warnings.
- Removal of inappropriate content.
- Temporary or permanent suspension of access to the project.

## How to Report Issues

If you witness behavior that violates this Code of Conduct, please report it to the project maintainers. You can do this by opening an issue in this repository or contacting one of the maintain


